data.name: LinkLabel3.Text
data.value: This pre-installation environment is not only used to install Windows. It contains many tools which can help you perform a computer maintenance or a software repair. Exit Setup If you want to launch Setup later, just click its shortcut on the desktop.

data.name: scText.Text
data.value:
The source code of this program can be found on GitHub.
- This project can be opened on Visual Studio 2012 and newer, without the need of conversion - The .NET Framework 4.8 Developer Pack must be installed to open this project
Do you want to suggest a new feature to be included in a future version? Have you experienced a bug you want to report? Don't hesitate on reporting feedback or (even better) contributing (you'll need a GitHub account). Your feedback is critical.
Do you want to enjoy the latest features? Check the Hummingbird branch! Weekly updates, new features and a sneak peek of the program's future

data.name: Label17.Text
data.value: A product key assures you have gotten a legitimate Windows copy. If you decide to link a Microsoft account later, the product key can be tied to it. A legitimately activated copy of Windows also gives you more security, and tranquility.

data.name: Label33.Text
data.value: In order to finish installation, your system needs to be restarted. Please wait 10 seconds, or if you do not want to wait, click "Restart now". You will need to remove the installation media. Please eject the installation DVD or USB drive after the countdown ends.

data.name: GRUBNotices.Text
data.value:
If a Linux distribution is installed on your system, and that installation came with GRUB as the bootloader, installing Windows may render GRUB inaccessible in favor of the Windows Boot Manager (BOOTMGR)
If that happens, boot to a live environment of the Linux distro you have installed, and install "grub-repair" If you want to learn more, go to this link:
